abstract: CHICAGO, April 30. A Cook County Farmers' Association was formed to-day, with a very large membership. Hon. John Wentworth was elected President. This association, although not a regular grange, is none the less a political society, the members having in caucus pledged themselves to vote only for those persons who are in sympathy with agricultural interests. It is claimed that the four or five granges in this county will soon, amalgamate with this association.
